How we will see in the future (?)
0 views posted 03 Aug 2012, 21:51 Hey fellas,
I just read something interesting, about what our view might look like in the future (not an affirmation, just an assumption) Here is the link. It's like an improved reality and would work as a medley between Google glasses and standard contact lenses : it's called Sight, created by two Israeli students. What is your opinion about it ? Going to / Not going to happen ? Good / Bad thing ?
IMO, at first sight, it looks pretty good and cool, but is it really what we need ? I sometimes wonder why humans want so much technology in their lifes... Also, if you're keen on such things, I recommend you the English miniserie Black Mirror, a must see (only 3 episodes, so give it a try) :)
