AhrimanThorn26328
• 04 Aug 2012, 03:00 Augmented reality already exists and it is only a matter of time before it does indeed switch from our phones and into our brains. I doubt that contact lenses will be how this technology is implemented however, since the use of lenses would seriously restrict the power of the tech. It will much more likely involve neural implants and will bypass the optic nerve all together and interact with the visual cortex. It would still work alongside normal vision though and would allow an overlay of data on top of the visually perceived world. We would believe we were seeing this overlay with our eyes but it would all take place in the brain.
The potential for misuse for this kind of tech is very great however because if you could hack into some ones visual cortex you could quite literally make them see whatever you wanted, and connectivity of the implant would be necessary for updating with new data. 2
