Mertado4685
• 04 August 2012, 06:25 Show comment
First: They simply ripped off the Matrix movies.
Second: That's an art/design project, not a tech project. I'm assuming it's a contact lens type of tech they're playing with (they don't say in the video, but it's implied).
Third: A similar technology has already been developed, tried, and abandoned because during testing it made everyone that used it physically ill. Direct brain stimulation is the only way this idea would work.
Last: Why would you want such a system if someone can hack into it and either see what you see or take control your body? I'm not a conspiracy nut by any stretch of the imagination, but unless the tech is modem-free (rendering it relatively useless), I don't see any sane person getting one.
Technology is supposed to be making our lives easier. That's its purpose. I'm waiting to see what kind of mental/physical disorders result from the massive information overload we now have available. Funny thing is we do it to ourselves, claiming it somehow enriches our lives.
Also, most people can't even drive without trying to text and/or call someone at the same time and look how many people that combination of activities kills each year.
Interesting, if not quite original, art project, but if getting a call is gonna hijack my vision while I'm in the middle of a bullfight, uhhhh. . . you can keep it. 1
